<br>
/cheer! Totally agreed. But Until we have some sort of utopian society, its not going to happen. :/<br>
<br>
You are right that Blizzard has made great PC games for a long while. However, they don't only make great PC games, they simply make great games.(hell, I still play Rock 'N Roll Racing on my SNES emu occasionally) The reason they have gotten so huge on PC, is that the great games they made were suited perfectly for PC's<br>
<br>
Certain types of games are suited to either PC's or Consoles. Fighting games, Rythym games, Platformers, Survival Horror games, just about all arcade-type games, Japanese style RPG's and these &quot;action-tactical&quot; games such as Metal gear solid, splinter cell, and Starcraft:ghost are more suited towards consoles. While RTS games, First Person Shooters, Turn based games, Simulations, American style RPG's and just about any other D&amp;D based game are more suited to PC's.<br>
<br>
I did play starcraft 64, and it sucks. The interface isn't that bad, but the game just ssslllooowwwsss down during huge battles. And for some reason it gave me a headache. There was also a warcraft two on the playstation. I never played it, but it did get good reviews. <br>
<br>
And as much sense as your point about microsoft makes, it isn't an xbox exclusive. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  If it was, you'd be sure microsoft would be shouting it from the rooftops. (Though they did just buy Rare from Nintendo,bleh. Very smart of them.)<br>
<br>
And about your last point, this game isn't going to keep that cycle of PC game's from happening. Blizzard has brought in an outside company(Nihilistic) to make the game, similar to what they did with diablo. So its not going to slow them down on the other games they are working on. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Finally, about Starcraft Two. I'm quite sure it is in development. Blizzard knows damn well that it will sell a million copies faster then you can say &quot;cha-ching&quot; in Korea alone. They're probably just taking their sweet time with the game, just like the original. <p>DiscoWliten<br>
