<br>
Youre totally right about Rock and Roll racing... damn that was a fun game, I had totally forgotten about it. However to say they make good games for PC AND consoles may be a little over the top. I think its safe to say that on consoles they are probably hit or miss at best. Ever play 'Death and Return of Superman' for SNES? P.U. What a stinker that one was. How about 'Lost Vikings 2'? I never played it but I never could figure out part 1 so who knows. What about 'Justice Leage Task Force'? Please. Anyways quite enough of that :P<br>
<br>
As for claiming that &quot;some games are good on consoles and some are good on PC...&quot;, I think that is quite silly. What is the one thing that every console owner has that the PC owner most likely does not? A controller. A simple, homogeneous, quality, reliable controller. Make a game that needs a controller (possibly comes with one), is high quality (as any Blizzard PC game is bound to be, they have a reputation), and has multiplayer support, and any of those game types you listed can be a big hit on the PC. Honestly Im not really sure why noone has done it before. The silly idea that for some reason a fighting game can &quot;only be good on a console&quot; is quite frustrating to someone like myself. Im consigned to going to the arcade to get my fix of 'Xmen vs StreetFighter' or whatnot. <br>
<br>
Anyways, I will not be purchasing a console just for the sake of owning another Blizzard title, but they could have guaranteed at least one more sale by porting it to PC. Just my 2 cents.<br>
